<docs>
	<doc for="LayoutEventHandler">
		<summary>
			<para>Represents the method that will handle the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.Control.Layout"/> event of a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.Control"/>.</para>
		</summary>
		<param name="sender">The source of the event.</param>
		<param name=" e">A <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.LayoutEventArgs"/> that contains the event data.</param>
		<remarks>
			<para>When you create a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.LayoutEventArgs"/> delegate, you identify the method that
   will handle the event. To associate the event with your event handler, add an
   instance of the delegate to the event. The event handler is called whenever the
   event occurs, unless you remove the delegate. For more information about event
   handler delegates, see <see topic="cpconEventsDelegates"/>.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<codelink SampleID="LayoutEventArgs" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.LayoutEventArgs"/>
